\frac64
2\sum_{n=2}^{\infty}\frac{1}{(n-1)(n+1)}=\frac{6}{4}
\frac2{(n+1)(n-1)}=\frac{n+1-(n-1)}{(n+1)(n-1)}=\frac1{n-1}-\frac1{n+1}
\frac{6}{4}=\frac{3}{2}
\left(\frac{1}{1}-\frac{1}{3}\right)+ \left(\frac{1}{2}-\frac{1}{4}\right)+ \left(\frac{1}{3}-\frac{1}{5}\right)+ \left(\frac{1}{4}-\frac{1}{6}\right)+\cdots =1+\frac{1}{2}=\frac{3}{2}
 2\sum_{n=2}^{\infty}\frac{1}{(n-1)(n+1)} =  \sum_{n=2}^{\infty}\frac{2}{(n-1)(n+1)}= \sum_{n=2}^{\infty}\left(\frac{1}{n-1}-\frac{1}{n+1}\right) =\\ \left[  \left(1 - \frac 13\right) + \left(\frac 12 - \frac 14\right)  + \left(\frac 13 - \frac 15\right) + \cdots \right] = \\ \left[  1 + \frac 12 + \left(\frac 13 - \frac 13\right) + \left(\frac 14 - \frac 14\right) + \cdots \right] = \frac 32 
